>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>- Department of Computer Information</li>\r\n<li>- Department of AI Convergence and Machinery</li>\r\n<li>- Department of Semiconductor and Electronics</li>\r\n<li>- Department of Hotel, Aviation, and Tourism</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 55.649px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-width: 0px; height: 55.649px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 72.5px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-width: 0px; height: 72.5px;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><strong>2. GET Overseas Employment Class by the Office of International Affairs</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 103.174px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border-width: 0px; height: 103.174px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"164\" data-end=\"196\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"166\" data-end=\"196\">- Recruiting students who wish to work in the U.S. or Japan and providing relevant training</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"197\" data-end=\"245\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"199\" data-end=\"245\">- Students complete their major coursework in their home department, while language and consulting programs are provided by the Office of International Affairs</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"246\" data-end=\"274\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"248\" data-end=\"274\">- Employment placements in the U.S. and Japan are arranged through the GET Center&rsquo;s overseas network</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>',1,'overseas-careers','english','2025-04-21 06:18:09.235695','2025-06-16 01:31:23.976819'),(194,'Notice of Application for the 2024 Global Field Study Program','<p data-start=\"876\" data-end=\"1038\">The Office of International Affairs is recruiting applicants for the Global Field Study Program from Thursday, February 8, 2024, to Friday, February 23, 2024!</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1040\" data-end=\"1131\">We encourage all enrolled students to apply and show interest in this exciting opportunity.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1040\" data-end=\"1131\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1138\" data-end=\"1180\">Global Field Study Program Information</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1184\" data-end=\"1507\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1184\" data-end=\"1507\">Program Overview:&nbsp;This program offers students the opportunity to gain language education and practical field experience in countries such as the United States, United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, and Japan. The program lasts for a total of 4 months: 2 months of language training followed by 2 months of internship.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1511\" data-end=\"1642\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1511\" data-end=\"1642\">Organizers:&nbsp;Ministry of Education (Republic of Korea), Korea Council for College Education, and Yeungjin University College</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1646\" data-end=\"1824\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1646\" data-end=\"1824\">Cost:&nbsp;Participation in the program is completely free of charge (funded by the government and the university). Note: Meals and personal living expenses are not covered.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1646\" data-end=\"1824\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1828\" data-end=\"2071\">Dispatch Schedule:&nbsp;Participants will be sent abroad for 4 months between May and December 2024. The exact departure time depends on the country and host institution, with most departures expected in May or between August and September.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"1828\" data-end=\"2071\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2075\" data-end=\"2091\">Eligibility:&nbsp;Enrolled students who have completed at least two semesters by the application date</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2186\" data-end=\"2296\">Students on leave of absence are not eligible (except those returning to school in the first semester of 2024)</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2186\" data-end=\"2296\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2303\" data-end=\"2334\">Screening Types (Important)</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2336\" data-end=\"2399\">Applicants can choose one of the following two screening types:</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"2336\" data-end=\"2399\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li data-start=\"2404\" data-end=\"2505\">Designated/General Track: For applicants who meet both language and academic score requirements</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"2404\" data-end=\"2505\">Open Track: For applicants who do not meet the language requirement. However, if you do not submit your language score by July, your participation will be canceled.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p data-start=\"2686\" data-end=\"2761\">Please refer to the next section for detailed eligibility requirements.</p>',1,'notice','english','2025-06-13 10:47:18.162700','2025-06-16 01:36:15.144170'),(195,'2024年度グローバル現場学習申請案内','<p data-start=\"96\" data-end=\"163\">国際交流院では、2024年2月8日（木）から2024年2月23日（金）まで、グローバル現場学習プログラムの参加者を募集します！</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"165\" data-end=\"193\">在学生の皆さんの多くの関心とご応募をお待ちしております。</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"220\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"220\">グローバル現場学習プログラム案内</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"200\" data-end=\"220\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"224\" data-end=\"340\">プログラム概要：学生がアメリカ、イギリス、カナダ、オーストラリア、日本などの海外で語学教育と現地実習を経験できる機会を提供します。プログラム期間は合計4ヶ月で、語学教育2ヶ月＋インターンシップ2ヶ月で構成されます。</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"344\" data-end=\"389\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"344\" data-end=\"389\">主催および主管機関：大韓民国教育部、韓国専門大学協議会、ヨンジン専門大学</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"393\" data-end=\"468\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"393\" data-end=\"468\">費用：プログラム参加費は全額無料です。（国庫および学校支援により負担）<br data-start=\"437\" data-end=\"440\">※ただし、食費および個人生活費は自己負担となります。</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"472\" data-end=\"568\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"472\" data-end=\"568\">派遣スケジュール：2024年5月から2024年12月の間で、4ヶ月間の海外派遣。派遣時期は派遣先の国や機関により異なりますが、主に5月または8月〜9月の出国を予定しています。</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"572\" data-end=\"581\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"572\" data-end=\"581\">参加資格：申請日基準で2学期以上を修了している在学生</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"614\" data-end=\"657\">休学中の学生は参加できません（ただし、2024年度第1学期に復学予定の学生は参加可能）</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"664\" data-end=\"678\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"664\" data-end=\"678\">選考区分案内（重要）</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"680\" data-end=\"707\">選考は、次の2つの区分から1つを選択して応募できます：</p>\r\n<ol data-start=\"709\" data-end=\"846\">\r\n<li data-start=\"709\" data-end=\"760\">\r\n<p data-start=\"712\" data-end=\"760\">指定／一般選考：<br data-start=\"724\" data-end=\"727\">語学成績および学校の成績の両方を満たす応募者を対象とします。</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start=\"762\" data-end=\"846\">\r\n<p data-start=\"765\" data-end=\"846\">オープン選考：<br data-start=\"776\" data-end=\"779\">語学成績を満たしていない応募者向けの選考です。<br data-start=\"805\" data-end=\"808\">※ただし、7月までに語学成績を提出しない場合は、派遣が取り消されます。</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p data-start=\"853\" data-end=\"886\">応募資格の詳細については、次のセクションをご確認ください。</p>',1,'notice','japanese','2025-06-13 10:59:50.146557','2025-06-16 01:36:15.144170'),(196,'Notice of Online Operation of the Global Zone/Center for the First Semester of 2024','<p data-start=\"92\" data-end=\"306\">The Office of International Affairs will operate the Global Zone/Center for the first semester of the 2024 academic year online as outlined below.<br data-start=\"242\" data-end=\"245\">We encourage active participation from all enrolled students.</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"92\" data-end=\"306\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"92\" data-end=\"306\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"92\" data-end=\"306\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"312\" data-end=\"366\">[Global Zone &ndash; Japanese / Global Center &ndash; English]</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"312\" data-end=\"366\"><img src=\"https://oic.yju.ac.kr/api/files//post-image/770fb255-9b79-4dc7-9260-254d3de251a0-1_.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"794\" height=\"1123\"></p>',1,'notice','english','2025-06-13 11:20:04.009761','2025-06-16 01:36:15.144170'),(197,'2024年度第1学期グローバルゾーン／センターオンライン運営案内','<p data-start=\"415\" data-end=\"499\">国際交流院では、2024年度第1学期のグローバルゾーン／センターを以下の通りオンラインで運営いたします。<br data-start=\"471\" data-end=\"474\">在学生の皆さんの積極的な参加をお待ちしております。</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"415\" data-end=\"499\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start=\"415\" 